## Session 2 тАФ C++ Backend (Initial Implementation)

Complete C++20 rewrite of the Python backend. All four bootloader backends,
platform detector, JSON IPC bridge, logger, backup, and main entry point.

### Bug fixes (Session 2 тАФ 12 fixes)

| # | Problem | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 19 | C++ backend crashed with "no bootloader detected" without root | Added `--demo` / `-d` flag and `MockBackend` in `main.cpp` |
| 20 | `PlatformDetector::isAppleSilicon()` used unreliable path proxy | Replaced with `uname()` checking `machine == "arm64"` |
| 21 | `PlatformDetector::commandExists()` always used `which` тАФ not valid on Windows | Uses `where` on Windows, `command -v` on Unix |
| 22 | `PlatformDetector::osName()` had no else branch тАФ uninitialised return | Added explicit `return "Unknown"` fallback |
| 23 | `Logger` and `Backup` used `getenv("HOME")` only тАФ wrong path on Windows | Added `SHGetFolderPathA(CSIDL_APPDATA)` on Windows; falls back to `temp_directory_path()` |
| 24 | `Backup::save()` and `list()` propagated `std::filesystem` exceptions uncaught | Wrapped in `try/catch`; errors returned as `Result::fail` |
| 25 | `Backup::list()` manual `.bak` suffix check was off-by-one prone | Replaced with `std::string::ends_with()` (C++20) |
| 26 | `BackendBridge::dispatch()` silently ignored requests with no `action` field | Now writes an error response immediately |
| 27 | `BackendBridge` `quit` called `std::exit(0)` mid-loop тАФ bypassed destructors and log flush | Changed to `std::cin.setstate(eofbit)` for clean loop exit |
| 28 | `BackendBridge::jsonGet()` did not handle whitespace after `:` or escaped quotes | Rewritten to skip whitespace and step over `\"` sequences |
| 29 | `Logger::timestamp()` used `char buf[32]` with `strftime` тАФ potential UB | Replaced with `std::ostringstream` + `std::put_time` |
| 30 | Uploaded `.cpp` files used `src/` include paths but were placed flat тАФ include resolution failed | Restructured into `src/`, `src/backends/`, `src/utils/` |

