## Session 6 тАФ Windows Build Fixes and Setup Script

### `setup_windows.bat` тАФ one-click Windows C++ setup
1. Auto-detects Visual Studio and calls `vcvars64.bat`
2. Checks for CMake; prints download URL if missing
3. Installs vcpkg to `C:\vcpkg` if not already there
4. Installs `glfw3:x64-windows` via vcpkg
5. Builds `blm-backend.exe` and `blm-gui.exe`; copies both to `run\`
6. Offers to launch in demo mode immediately

### Bug fixes (Session 6)

| # | Problem | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 41 | `find_package(PkgConfig REQUIRED)` hard-fails on Windows тАФ `pkg-config` does not exist in MSVC/vcpkg environments | Platform-aware GLFW detection: `find_package(glfw3 CONFIG REQUIRED)` on Windows, `pkg_check_modules` on Linux/macOS |
| 42 | `::` comments fail in PowerShell; wrong relative paths; `build.bat` not found | Added `setup_windows.bat` which handles everything from the correct directory |

