## Session 30 тАФ FLTK GUI Overhaul + pygame Retired

### Decision: FLTK is now the default Python GUI

pygame GUI (`gui_pygame.py`) kept for reference but no longer the default.
`blm.py` now defaults to the FLTK GUI.

Reasons: FLTK is a proper native widget toolkit using OS-native controls;
pyFLTK has prebuilt wheels for Windows and macOS; pygame requires a full
game-library stack for what is essentially a form-based tool; FLTK renders
crisper, more professional-looking UI on all platforms.

### FLTK GUI fixes (4 issues from photo review)

#### 1. Set Default button тАФ correctly enabled when an entry is selected

All 7 buttons now use a single `style(btn, enabled, color)` helper that sets
both `color()` and `labelcolor()` consistently. Previously Set Default's enabled
state was not updating on selection change.

#### 2. Log tab тАФ Clear button below log box; font size increased

Log box fills `h - BTN_H - GAP*2` pixels; Clear button sits below at `y + log_h + GAP`.
Log text font size increased from 11 to 13.

#### 3. Settings tab тАФ full sections implemented

Old: one checkbox + two static lines.
New: four sections: GENERAL SETTINGS, MODE & STATUS, FILE PATHS, BACKEND & PLATFORM.

**GENERAL SETTINGS:** 3 checkboxes тАФ Confirm dialogs, Create backups, Show technical metadata.

**MODE & STATUS:** Live/demo shown in green/amber; privilege status (write access confirmed /
run as Administrator/root). Both lines live-updated on every refresh.

**FILE PATHS:** Log and backups paths, platform-aware (`%APPDATA%` on Windows,
`~/.config` on Linux/macOS).

**BACKEND & PLATFORM:** Backend name, kind, and full support matrix table
(GRUB2, systemd-boot, Windows BCD, macOS).

#### 4. Platform tab removed тАФ merged into Settings

Tab count reduced from 4 to 3: Boot Entries | Settings | Log.

### Other improvements

- `[default]` and `[ro]` tags in entry list (ASCII, no Unicode)
- All 7 action buttons equal-width, filling the full window width
- Window size increased to 980├Ч660 for better readability
- Duplicate placeholder button creation removed

