## Session 33 тАФ FLTK Settings: Garbled Support Matrix + Reset Button

### Bug 67 тАФ Support matrix rendered as garbage text on Windows

**File:** `python/gui_fltk.py`

The BACKEND & PLATFORM support matrix showed `yiOk^B`, `c┬йOk^B` etc.

**Root cause:** Three separate `Fl_Box` widgets per row were created inside
a `_mkcol` helper. pyFLTK stores a pointer to the C string of the label.
When the Python string passed to `Fl_Box(...)` was a temporary not stored
in a named variable, it was garbage collected immediately, leaving the widget
with a dangling pointer that read as garbage bytes on Windows MSVC builds.

**Fix:** Replaced three `Fl_Box` widgets per row with one `Fl_Box` per row
using a plain concatenated string with `.ljust()` for alignment. Also replaced
all f-string format specs (`f"{x:<18}"`) with `.ljust()` throughout тАФ
FLTK on some platforms misinterprets certain byte sequences in format strings.

### Added: "Reset to defaults" button

Appears at the bottom of the Settings tab. Resets all three settings to `True`,
saves to `settings.json`, and updates the checkboxes visually.

