## Session 34 тАФ C++ Nuklear GUI: Full Parity with FLTK GUI

### Changes

#### 1. Tab bar: 4 tabs тЖТ 3 tabs

Old: `Boot Entries | Platform | Settings | Log`
New: `Boot Entries | Settings | Log`

Platform tab content (backend name, kind, writable status, support matrix) moved into
the Settings tab under BACKEND & PLATFORM тАФ identical to the FLTK GUI layout.

#### 2. Settings tab: 3 checkboxes + Reset button

Old: 1 checkbox (confirm dialogs only)
New: 3 checkboxes:
- **Confirm before Set Default and Delete** тАФ wired to `confirmOps`
- **Create backups before writing changes** тАФ wired to `backupOps`
- **Show technical metadata in entry details** тАФ wired to `showMeta`

**Reset to defaults** button resets all three to `true` and logs the action.

```cpp
bool confirmOps = true;   // confirm before set-default and delete
bool backupOps  = true;   // create timestamped backups before writes
bool showMeta   = true;   // show kernel/uuid/partition in detail
```

#### 3. Detail panel respects `showMeta` setting

When "Show technical metadata" is unchecked, Kernel, Partition, UUID, and Config
fields are hidden. Only Name and Type are always shown. Matches FLTK GUI behaviour.

#### 4. Linux one-click build script: `gui-nuklear/build_linux.sh`

- Detects missing SDL2 and auto-installs via `apt`, `dnf`, `pacman`, or `brew`
- Builds both `blm-backend` and `blm-gui-nuklear` silently
- Copies both binaries into `run/` with correct permissions
- Offers to launch in demo mode immediately

```bash
chmod +x gui-nuklear/build_linux.sh
./gui-nuklear/build_linux.sh
./run/blm-gui-nuklear --demo    # test without root
sudo ./run/blm-gui-nuklear      # real mode
```

